 Pazopanib inhibits the growth of blood vessels in tumors by inhibiting a protein called vascular endothelial growth factor (commonly called VEGF).

 Pazopanib is not currently approved by the US Food and Drug Administration (FDA) and therefore considered an experimental medication.

 High levels of VEGF cause blood vessels to leak fluid, increasing the pressure in tumors similar to the increased pressure in lymphedema.

 Previous studies have found that treatment with pazopanib decreases the fluid pressure in tumors.

 That is why we think pazopanib might be an effective treatment for lymphedema.

